Python Chatbot

A simple chatbot built using Python. The chatbot interacts with users through a text-based interface and responds to common greetings, questions, and basic conversations.

Features
Interactive text-based conversation
Responds to greetings and common questions
Simple rule-based responses
Easy-to-use console interface
Exit command to end the chat

Technologies Used:
Python

How to Run:
Clone or download the project.
Open a terminal in the project folder.
Run the following command:
python chatbot.py
Type your messages and chat with the bot.
Enter bye or exit to end the conversation.

About the Project

This project was created to practice basic Python concepts such as conditional statements, loops, functions, string handling,
and user input processing. 
It demonstrates how simple rule-based chatbots work and serves as a foundation for building more advanced 
conversational applications in the future.
